CatDescriptText: Alex Lee, partner, Lee's Florists, 2117 Centre Avenue, was part of the Pittsburgher's Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 5, 1959 with question: "Do you believe Allegheny County Democrats and Republicans have selected their best candidates for public offices in past 10 years?"  Answer reads: "I think competition has been so keen that both parties have been forced to present their best candidates."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Alex Lee wearing eyeglasses, smoking cigar, standing on sidewalk in front of telephone pole, with buildings on the left, and a car in street on the right, possibly Centre Avenue
